benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account audit logs with history by account id

covered: Valid Request: Successful retrieval for valid accountId with expected 200 and application/json content type (TC01).
Empty Response: Case when account exists but has no audit logs and returns an empty JSON array (TC02).
Non-existent Resource: 404 response for account not found (TC03).
Input Validation: Invalid accountId format and partial accountId cases covered (TC04, TC17).
Authorization: Missing and expired/invalid token cases returning 401 are covered (TC05, TC06).
Server Errors / Dependency Failures: Internal server error (database unavailable) and degraded dependency scenarios covered (TC07, TC13).
Security: SQL injection attempt in path parameter is tested to ensure no sensitive leakage and safe failure (TC10).
Performance / Load: Large dataset and concurrent requests/performance checks are included (TC09, TC11).
Regression / Schema: Tests to ensure mandatory audit log fields and previously fixed bugs are asserted (TC12).
Edge Cases: Whitespace, uppercase, and maximum-length UUID handling covered (TC14, TC15, TC16).
Unsupported Parameters: Test for ignoring unsupported query parameters (TC08).
gaps: Pagination: No tests verify pagination behavior or parameters (limit/offset/page) for large result sets; TC09 asserts "all audit logs" but does not exercise paginated endpoints or limits.
Caching Behavior / Conditional Requests: No tests validate caching headers (ETag, Last-Modified, Cache-Control) or conditional GET semantics (304 Not Modified).
Authorization Granularity / Forbidden (403): No tests for insufficient permissions / forbidden access (403) or role-based access control.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: Concurrent/performance tests exist but there are no explicit rate-limiting tests (e.g., 429 responses under throttling).
Response Schema Validation Depth: While presence of required fields is asserted, there are no negative/field-level schema tests for unexpected/malformed field values or types.
Content-Encoding / Media Types: No tests for content negotiation, Accept header variations, or incorrect Content-Type handling.
Error Response Structure: Tests assert presence of error message but do not assert consistent error schema/fields (code, message, details, timestamps).
Boundary/performance SLA specifics: Performance tests mention thresholds but do not define/assert measurable SLA values or behavior under sustained load.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include queries with page/limit/offset (or whatever pagination scheme the API uses), verify correct subsets, total counts, links (next/prev) and behavior when requesting out-of-range pages.
Add caching/conditional GET tests: verify ETag/Last-Modified headers are present, conditional requests return 304 when unchanged, and Cache-Control is appropriate.
Add authorization role/permission tests: include scenarios where authenticated user lacks permission and assert 403 responses and proper error bodies.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests: simulate bursts to trigger 429 responses and verify Retry-After header behavior and graceful degradation.
Enhance schema validation tests: validate field types, required vs optional fields, and negative cases where fields are missing/incorrect types; assert consistent error schema on failures.
Add content negotiation and header handling tests: request with different Accept headers and assert proper Content-Type; send malformed Accept/Content-Type to verify robust error handling.
Standardize error response assertions: assert structured error payload (fields like code, message, and details) and avoid only free-text checks.
Quantify performance SLAs: define acceptable response-time thresholds for large-history and concurrent tests and assert against them to make performance tests actionable.
